All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
ArriveEvent
ArriveEvent represents a new Event with a Customer that has just arrived.
Customer
Customer only has an id tagged to him.
DoneEvent
DoneEvent is a Event that is at the last possible state, after Customer is served.
Event
An Event is an action that could produce a new event and change the status of servers.
EventComparator
CustomerComparator sorts customers based on time then ID.
LeaveEvent
LeaveEvent represents a Event with a Customer that is leaving.
Main
Main is the client who provides customers.
ServeEvent
ServeEvent represents a Customer that is being served.
Server
Server's job is to serve, reject, wait, finish serving customers.
Shop
Shop contains all the servers.
Simulator
Simulator handles a priority queue of events and updates the servers and queue based on the server's response.
Stats
Keeps track of statistics of simulator.
WaitEvent
ArriveEvent represents a Event with a Customer that is waiting.
